@node main "AssignPrefs V1.02 - Contents"
@next overview

This is the documentation file for the AssignPrefs program. Select one of
the following topics:

  @{" Overview         " link overview }  Gives you a brief overview
  @{" Requirements     " link requirements }  What you need to run AssignPrefs
  @{" Legal Stuff      " link legal }  Copyright and disclaimer
  @{" Installation     " link install }  How to install AssignPrefs
  @{" Workbench Usage  " link wbusage }  How to run AssignPrefs from Workbench
  @{" CLI Usage        " link cliusage }  How to run AssignPrefs from CLI
  @{" Operation        " link operation }  Detailed description of AssignPrefs
  @{" Startup-Sequence " link sseq }  How to use AssignPrefs in startup-sequence
  @{" Known Bugs       " link bugs }  Known bugs and problems
  @{" History          " link history }  What has changed

Before using AssignPrefs you _MUST_ read the @{" Legal Stuff " link legal} chapter.

@endnode main

@node overview "AssignPrefs - Overview"
@prev main
@toc main
@next requirements

If you use assigns in your startup-sequence you will pretty soon have a very
large file. AssignPrefs simplifies this by reducing all assign calls into
just one. With AssignPrefs, you can enter a number of assigns, save them in a
file and assign them by a simple programm call in startup-sequence, or by
double clicking on the icon.

AssignPrefs can be used from Workbench or CLI. It uses a full GadTools GUI
to edit your list of assigns, and it stores these lists with or without an
icon. If saved with an icon, you can assign the list by double clicking on
the project icon. For further detail, see @{" Workbench Usage " link wbusage}.

AssignPrefs can also be used to make assigns for games, applications etc.
You can save the assigns in the program's directory, and before running the
program, you can make the assigns it needs by double clicking the icon.

AssignPrefs also supports assignment now availible in 37: Late, Add and Path.
For mor detail, see @{ " Operation " link operation}.

@endnode overview

@node requirements "AssignPrefs - Requirements"
@prev overviw
@next legal
@toc main

To use AssignPrefs, you need the following:

    - An Amiga Computer
    - Kickstart 37 or higher (haven't tested with 36, won't run with 34)
    - Workbench at least 2.0

@endnode requirements

